data.text:
This is a very good hardcover with dust jacket. First Edition August 1996 Del Ray Books. This copy is still crisp and clean inside and out. NOTE: Previous owners embossed stamp neatly place on title page, see photo. Rest of pages are still crisp and clean with no other markings seen. Illustrated maps inside front and back endpapers. The binding is tight and straight. Green hardcover boards with black quarter trim under dust jacket are very good with barely a hint of shelf wear. The accompanying dust jacket is clean and shiny with only very light shelf wear corners/edges. Standard medium octavo book size or 6.5" x 9.5" with 436 pages.

The Waterborn is the first novel from author J. Gregory Keyes. It takes readers into a world of myth and magic. In this land, The River flowed through and the River God held dominion. When a favorite cousin of the Imperial Princess disappeared, the princess searched through the land of the River, its ghosts and priests, giants and frightening creatures to find her cousin. But the princess wished for a hero.... and far away, a hero's journey would begin.
